The paper presents a motion planning algorithm for robots with kinodynamic constraints, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The algorithm uses optimization techniques to find an optimal path, which could also fall under the category of control systems (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques to improve the algorithm, which could fall under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper provides experimental results using robot models, which could fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) or computer vision (cs.CV) if the models were trained using visual data.
